Gardiner's debut solo release was a single co-written with Numan called "Stormtrooper in Drag" b/w "Night Talk" in 1981.
Gardiner's recording of The Velvet Underground's "Venus in Furs" was the first release on Numan's own label, Numa, in 1984.

Paul Gardiner struggled with heroin addiction in his last years and died at the age of 25 from an overdose of valium and dicanol combined with cold weather on 18 February 1984 in Limetrees Park in Northolt, Greater London.
Gary Numan wrote the song "A Child with the Ghost" (from the 1984 album Berserker) in memory of his friend and former bass-player.
